Title: r.series.interp
Abstract: Interpolates raster maps located (temporal or spatial) in between input raster maps at specific sampling positions.

Input.Abstract: Data point position for each input map
Input file with one input raster map name and data point position per line, field separator between name and sample point is 'pipe'
Name for output raster map (comma separated list if multiple)
Sampling point position for each output map (comma separated list)
Input file with one output raster map name and sample point position per line, field separator between name and sample point is 'pipe'
Interpolation method, currently only linear interpolation is supported

Accepted data types.str: as string representation of int, e.g. '1'
as comma delimited list of x min, x max, y min, y max. E.g. '4,10,101,105'
layer ID. Extent of layer is used.
layer name. Extent of layer is used.
layer source. Extent of layer is used.

Accepted data types.QgsGeometry: bounding box of geometry is used

Input.Abstract: GRASS GIS 7 region cellsize (leave 0 for default)
